<div id="aol-comments-BIdxKg" class="comment">
<div class="comment-body ">
<b class="display-name"> Mike </b>
<p>I manage cloud systems for corporate Amaerica, and someday cloud may impact MS, but not for a long time. Currently MS is a cloud leader. Also, MS SW is huge in the cloud (along with Open Source) so MS can sell to cloud companies or corporate . . . no matter. Cloud can save money but it has other risks and complexities. Such as if the WAN goes down so does your company. If the cloud company has an outage (and they do) many companies are impacted.<br/>Edison was not about centralized or decentralized. He was about providing a solution based on availalbe tech.<br/><br/>Internal corporate IT jobs will have the biggest impact or displacement. Today it takes 6 moths to spin-up a server with new tech in corporate America. At a cloud facility I can spin-up in hours. Cloud systems require a lot less peple than corporate America to maintain the infrastructure. Good or bad, cloud will be the next big thing like off shore.</p>
<b class="comment-meta">
<b class="date">March 25 2012 at 10:21 AM</b>
