<b class="display-name"> AngryUzer </b>
<p>This article is pointless as the cloud computing itself. They crating something that nobody even needs so they can sell it to people that don't know their heads from their feet and make money out of them.<br/>Cloud computing is to store your data on their servers and then you'll get it from these servers when you need it but you still need Internet or else you can't get your data. So they are just selling you space for storage, that's it. And they can snoop also on your data in their servers and know what you're doing and so on..<br/>Why would I need their storage space when a tiny hard drive with 1.5 terabytes costs 2 pennies in the store? and that I can use to retrieve my data even if I have no Internet. and I don't have anything to store anyway.<br/>Greedy and stupid financial engineering that scams fool people that know nothing but going with the flow.</p>
